What you need to know:

Tottenham and Palace were the big losers this weekend, but there is already a consensus among coaches that something needs to be done now to prevent farcical scenes from continuing all season.Joel Ward was harshly penalised for Everton's winner in a 2-1 victory at Selhurst Park leaving Palace manager Roy Hodgson despairing for the game he's been involved in for over 50 years.